race.comment: CHEEKY SORT (8) had support at Kembla Grange on debut and was only beaten 1.5 lengths over 1000m. Has the inside barrier and plenty of upside and can open her account. NOBLE RUBY (5) resumed in the same race, beaten less than 1L from the front. Has to skip over from a wide gate, but with the extra fitness she's a chance if that's achieved economically. MELODIA PERFECTA (4) has been freshened following a switch from the sharp Begg stable in Victoria. She's placed both starts this preparation on synthetic tracks and has turf figures just as good. Rates well and the betting will be key. BRUTAL ADVANCE (1) resumes and has switched from a Queensland yard. He draws low and has raced well in stronger than this. Wary of him.
